description:
A young woman travels to mysterious Castle Dunbar to investigate the death of her sister, under the guise of writing a book about the family that lives there. Nothing in the Castle is as it seems, and the ghost of her dead sister may yet roam the halls...

This is the first issue of the retitled series, continuing on from Sinister House of Secret Love.

description:
Features:

The Curse of the MacIntyres

Following the death of her father, Rachel travels to Scotland to stay with her mysterious relations, the MacIntyres. However, all is not as it seems in their crumbling gothic mansion, and Rachel soon finds herself caught up in deadly machinations.

The Strange Case of Patience Worth (a text story)

A Night to Remember -- A Day to Forget!

Louise travels to a house once inhabited by the lover of a distant ancestor of hers. Ghostly happenings begin to unfurl around her, attempting to separate her from her beloved Tony.
name: Curse of the MacIntyres

volume.name: The Sinister House of Secret Love

description:
To Wed the Devil

Sarah is forced to travel to far Bohemia to wed a man who she doesn't know in order to save her impoverished father. But what dark secrets lurk in the castle of the mysterious Baron Dumont?
name: To Wed The Devil

volume.name: The Sinister House of Secret Love

description:
Features:

The Bride of the Falcon

Summoned to Venice by the mysterious man with whom she has fallen in love via mail correspondence, Kathy soon discovers that everything is not as it seems.

Will I Ever See You Again (a text story)
name: The Bride of the Falcon

volume.name: The Sinister House of Secret Love

description:
Features:

Kiss of the Serpent

Following the deaths of her parents, American Michelle Harlinson travels to India, where she finds work as the governess of a wealthy man's niece and nephew. Soon sinister events force her to reconsider her decision to stay, and her growing feelings for the mysterious man.
name: Kiss of the Serpent

volume.name: The Sinister House of Secret Love

description: In a Victorian-era tale of magic and romance, young Tristran Thorn falls in love with the town beauty and must go on an incredible coming-of-age journey in order to capture her heart. Living in the small countryside town of Wall, one night Tristran vows to his beloved to retrieve a fallen star that they witnessed crashing down from the heavens. Now to gain his love's hand, he must leave behind his home and embark on a journey that will define the meaning of true love. Told through breathtaking painted illustrations, this fairytale for adults is a true masterpiece in storytelling storytelling.

volume.name: Neil Gaiman and Charles Vess' Stardust

description:

description:
Tristran Thorn's falling star has turned out to be a very angry young woman, crippled by a broken leg and mysteriously bound to carry the very object that caused her injury. With little understanding of what he faces, Tristran must begin his journey back to the village of Wall--and retain his nerve as sinister forces vying for the star converge on a mountain inn.
